      <head>Bertha [Berta] Jahn-Beer</head>

      <p>Pianist and teacher in Vienna.</p>

      <div>
        <head>Career summary</head>
        <p>Jahn-Beer taught piano at the Akademie/Hochschule f√ºr Musik und darstellende Kunst
          (formerly Vienna Conservatory of Music) between 1927 and 1938, losing her post as a
          consequence of the annexation of Austria to Germany by the National Socialists. Among
          others, she taught Hans Tischler while there.</p>
      </div>


      <div>
        <head>Jahn-Beer and Schenker</head>
        <p>The entry in Schenker's diary for April 3, 1907 seems to imply that Schenker accepted
          Jahn-Beer as his pupil (no lessonbooks exists from that time by which to verify this).
        </p>
      </div>
